The paper presents a new approach for duplicate detection in sliding windows using Bloom filters, which is a data structure commonly used in computer science for approximate membership queries. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses space and time complexity, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DB (Databases) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper mentions hardware-based implementations, which could place it in cs.DC (Digital Circuits) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
